import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['US_Gross'], data['Worldwide_Gross'])
    plt.xlabel('US_Gross')
    plt.ylabel('Worldwide_Gross')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['Production_Budget'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Production Budget')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Production_Budget?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.gca()
    data['IMDB_Rating'].plot(kind='box')
    median = data['IMDB_Rating'].median()
    plt.axhline(y=median, color='r', linestyle='-', label=f'Median: {median:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of IMDB_Rating?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    running_time_min = data['Running_Time_min']
    plt.hist(running_time_min, bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Running Time (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Running_Time_min?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
